[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ballymena crash victim is named as Yvonne Richmond

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The woman who died after being hit by a car in Ballymena, County Antrim, on Friday night has been named as Yvonne Richmond.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 70-year-old was from the Ballykeel area of the town.
She was walking her dog on the Galgorm Road at about 21:00 BST when the collision happened.
It took place close to the junction with Dans Road and only one vehicle was involved. The pensioner's dog was also killed.
